TO: WALTER J. MINTON

CC, 1 p.





Goldwin Smith Hall

Ithaca, N.Y.

January 12, 1958

Dear Mr. Minton,

Many thanks for your letter.

I do not think I would go to court for the sake of the foreign-language rights: they represent a minor matter, not worth the effort or the expense.

Nor would I under any circumstances go to a French court. I would rather follow a cour